│ THOUGHT: Now let me apply a simpler fix. The issue is that when `onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)` is true, we expect to have either a vector value or a single scalar value. But we have multiple  │
│ scalar values. The fix should be to allow multiple scalar values as long as we have a value at lane 0.                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Actually, looking at the code flow: when we call `get(Def, true)` with `NeedsScalar=true`, we always get lane 0. So even if there are scalar values for other lanes, we're only accessing │
│ lane 0. That should be fine.                                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ The assertion is checking that we're not in an inconsistent state. But having multiple scalar values when only lane 0 is used is not necessarily inconsistent. It might be wasteful, but  │
│ not wrong.                                                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Let me change the assertion to just check that we have a scalar value at lane 0.                                                                                                          │
